Dr J. A. F. (Jack) Garrick (fl. 1953-) is a prominent ichthyologist from New Zealand. He specialized in elasmobranchs and published many books and articles about shark and ray biology. He is the species authority for several types of sharks, including the New Zealand lanternshark. Garrick was a zoology professor at Victoria University of Wellington, appointed to a personal chair in 1971.[1]
